<div>		



<span class="section_title">New Home Recording Technologies Showcased At 2005 International CES Studio@Home Display </span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/2/2004</i></strong>
<br><br>
The latest home recording technologies will be showcased at the 2005 International CES, the world's largest annual tradeshow for consumer technology, January 6-9, 2005 in Las Vegas, Nevada.  The Studio@Home exhibit, sponsored by CMP Information and located in the CES South Plaza outside of the Las Vegas Convention Center, will feature new home recording and editing products, electronic music software, DJ equipment, keyboards and virtual musical instruments and desktop video editing and production tools.
<p>
Companies participating in the Studio@Home Showcase include:  AMD Computer, Auralex Acoustics, Creative Labs, Harps.com Corporation, HighAndes, Mackie, Marshall Electronics, M-Audio, PreSonus Audio Electronics and Steinberg.  
<p> 
"The next generation of home recording products on display at the Studio@Home exhibit  combines the best of both worlds, power and affordability, that makes them so appealing to consumers," said Karen Chupka, vice president of conferences and events for CEA, the producer of the International CES.  "These technologies are now accessible to a wider audience than ever before and this cool new display will help educate attendees on the best ways to record their own CDs, DVDs and live performances.  Exhibits like this, that showcase interesting and exciting technologies, are part of what makes the International CES such a must-attend industry event."
<p>
The Studio@Home exhibit is one of more than 20 TechZones at the 2005 International CES. Seventeen of the TechZones will be located in the new CES Central and South Plazas, with the highest concentration located in Innovations Plus in the CES Central Plaza outside the Las Vegas Convention Center.  Tech Zones in this area include those focusing on Bluetooth, Cardio Play, RFID, and TechHome.  In addition to housing the Tech Zones, Innovations Plus also features the 2005 International CES Innovations honorees displays.  
<p>
Joining Studio@Home in the South Plaza are the HD Pro Showcase, sponsored by Sony, which highlights the latest advances in high definition television production and broadcast technologies and the NextGen Home exhibit.
<p>
For a complete list of TechZones, please visit www.cesweb.org/techzones.  For more news on CES before, during and after the show, go to www.CESweb.org, the interactive source for CES information.
<p>
Note to Journalists:  Journalists are encouraged to arrive in Las Vegas by Tuesday, January 4, 2005 to take advantage of all the CES press conferences and events.  CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES will run January 4 from 4:00 p.m. to 7:00 p.m. in the Las Vegas Convention Center, room S226, across the hallway from the CES Press Room.  A list of press room hours and services is posted at www.CESweb.org.
<p>

About CEA: <br>
The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the consumer technology industry through technology policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.  CEA represents more than 1,800 corporate members involved in the design, development, manufacturing, distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline communications, information technology, home networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services that are sold through consumer channels. Combined, CEA's members account for more than $90 billion in annual sales.  CEA's resources are available online at www.CE.org, the definitive source for information about the consumer electronics industry. <br>
CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Defining Tomorrow's Technology.  All profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.

